 (1878), p. 562\xe2\x80\x9365</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-wikisource-48"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-wikisource_48-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a class="external text" href="http://de.wikisource.org/wiki/Nicolaus_Coppernicus_aus_Thorn_%C3%BCber_die_Kreisbewegungen_der_Weltk%C3%B6rper/Vorwort#Orthographie">Maximilian Curtze, <i>Ueber die Orthographie des Namens Coppernicus</i>, 1879</a></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Polish_Literature_p._38-50"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Polish_Literature_p._38_50-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Polish_Literature_p._38_50-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Polish_Literature_p._38_50-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Czes%C5%82aw_Mi%C5%82osz" title="Czes\xc5\x82aw Mi\xc5\x82osz">Czes\xc5\x82aw Mi\xc5\x82osz</a>, <i>The History of Polish Literature</i>, p. 38.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-armitage55-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-armitage55_52-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Angus Armitage, <i>The World of Copernicus</i>, p. 55.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-psb4-5-53"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-psb4-5_53-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Dobrzycki and Hajdukiewicz (1969), pp. 4\xe2\x80\x935.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-54"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-54">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Sobel (2011), pp. 7, 232.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-55"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-55">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Jerzy Dobrzycki and Leszek Hajdukiewicz, "Kopernik, Miko\xc5\x82aj", <i><a href="/wiki/Polski_s%C5%82ownik_biograficzny" class="mw-redirect" title="Polski s\xc5\x82ownik biograficzny">Polski s\xc5\x82ownik biograficzny</a></i> (Polish Biographical Dictionary), vol. XIV, Wroc\xc5\x82aw, <a href="/wiki/Poli